.TH man 8 "30 May 2018" "0.1.0" "shy man page"
.SH NAME
shy \- inspecting bash scripts 
.SH SYNOPSIS
shy [command][file]
.SH DESCRIPTION
GNU shy is a program that inspects bash files for issues like:
-Deprecated syntax
-Outdated syntax
-Invalid syntax 
.SH OPTIONS
Enter the command then the file.
.br
-i, --inspect    Inspect the script for issues.
.br
-v, --version    Display shy version and exit.
.br
-h, --help       Describe command-line options and exit.
.br
-c               Print commentary.
.br
-C               Print copyright.
.br
-d               Print dependency tree of scripts that are sourced from the script.
.SH SEE ALSO
info shy 
.SH BUGS
No known bugs.
.SH AUTHOR
Artyom Poptsov <artyom-poptsom@gmail.com>,
